# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# enqueue/drain SCRIPT secrets — for running `task newsletter:*` locally.
# Copy to `newsletter/.env` (gitignored) and fill in.
#
# These mirror the GitHub Actions secrets used by the workflows:
#     GITHUB_TOKEN   ←→  Actions secret NEWSLETTER_DATA_TOKEN
#     BREVO_API_KEY  ←→  Actions secret BREVO_API_KEY
# In CI you set those in the repo (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions),
# NOT in any file.
#
# Only SECRETS live here. Non-secret config (DATA_REPO, MAIL_FROM_*,
# WORKER_PUBLIC_URL, …) is read automatically from worker/wrangler.toml, so
# there is nothing to keep in sync. No Turnstile key is needed here — the
# scripts don't verify Turnstile, only the Worker does.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Data-repo access. Fine-grained GitHub PAT, scoped to the private data repo,
# Contents: Read and write. (Same value as the Worker's GITHUB_TOKEN secret.)
GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_xxx

# Email provider API key (current provider: Brevo).
# Where: Brevo → SMTP & API → API Keys (a transactional key).
BREVO_API_KEY=xkeysib-xxx

# Optional one-off overrides (env wins over wrangler.toml). Usually unset:
# DATA_REPO=you/test-data
# DAILY_BUDGET=5
